Maintenance Technician

Company: Adecco USA
Location: Portland
Posted on: December 31, 2020

Job Description:

Adecco is assisting a local manufacturing facility, seeking a 1 st Shift Maintenance Technician in Portland, ME. This is a temp-to-hire or permanent/direct hire opportunity paying $21 - $23 per hour, plus the possibility of incentives and overtime. Schedule - Monday - Friday - 5:45AM - 2:15PM + possible call schedule Essential Functions:

* Perform electrical / mechanical maintenance, repairs and installation for equipment and facilities
* Troubleshoot and repair electrical / electronic and programmable equipment
* Understand equipment schematics
* Ability to use electrical, electronic and programmable controller testing and diagnosing equipment
* Ability to do basic circuit design as part of repair and installation procedures
* Install electrical utilities - meeting all state, local and federal codes
* Working knowledge of lockout/ tagout procedures and appropriate OSHA standards
* Mechanical troubleshooting and repair capabilities are a plus
* Inspect /clean tanks and lines in machines and equipment
* Support and work with production departments' and engineering personnel to continually improve Division TPM (total productive maintenance) program
* Detect and report improper operation, faulty equipment, defective materials and unsafe &amp; unusual conditions to supervisor with improvement suggestions
* Maintain necessary records
* Maintain work area and equipment in a clean and orderly condition
* Follow prescribed safety rules and regulations and maintain quality standards
* Train and mentor less experienced co -workers
* Work with Engineering to rebuild, design, and upgrade new existing equipment.
* Adhere to strict safety and cleanliness standards. Benefits:
* 401(k)
* 401(k) Matching
* Dental Insurance
* Disability Insurance
* Flexible Spending Account
* Health Insurance
* Health Savings Account
* Life Insurance
* Paid Time Off
* Retirement Plan
* Tuition Reimbursement
* Vision Insurance If you are interested in this position, please apply to this posting with your resume or call our office at (207) 772-2882 for more details!Equal Opportunity Employer/Veterans/DisabledTo read our Candidate Privacy Information Statement, which explains how we will use your information, please The Company will consider qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records
